BRL says trading ok , small deals planned . Australia ' s second largest wine producer BRL Hardy Ltd said on Thursday it had ruled out any major acquisitions in the near future but was close to completing two smaller deals . " One within a month , if the other comes to fruition an announcement may be within a couple of months , " managing director Stephen Millar said . He also said the first three months of calendar 1997 had been very pleasing and the company was in line with analysts forecasts for double digit profit growth . Asked about the impending deals , Millar would not say if they were direct acquisitions or joint ventures . 
